  "body": "### Description\r\nStore state as merkle trie nodes so that we can store every state without increasing database size too much.\r\n\r\n## Key Tasks\r\n\r\n* [x] Introduce new database format that allows storing state leaf and branch nodes in new columns\r\n* [x] Consider making the finalized state storage mechanism pluggable to avoid duplicating the rest of finalized dao code\r\n* [x] Dao code to store trie nodes (skip storing leaf nodes with data < hash size)\r\n* [x] Dao code to load trie nodes (return hash if leaf not found)\r\n* [ ] Add --X config option to specify the max number of trie levels to compress\r\n* [x] Support iterating trie nodes, compressing levels as appropriate\r\n    * [x] Generic iterate with max compression depth function to handle branch nodes (then delegate to specific implementation for nodes at target depth)\r\n    * [x] Containers (SszCompositeSchema or maybe AbstractSszContainerSchema)\r\n    * [x] Lists (AbstractSszListSchema)\r\n    * [x] Vectors (AbstractSszVectorSchema)\r\n    * [x] Primitives (AbstractSszPrimitiveSchema) Including trimming data to correct length\r\n* [x] Skip iterating nodes if the branch has already been stored (need to store child nodes prior to the branch? - maybe transactions avoid problems here)\r\n* [x] Reload trie nodes (with lazy loading?)\r\n    * [x] Containers (SszCompositeSchema or maybe AbstractSszContainerSchema)\r\n    * [x] Lists (AbstractSszListSchema)\r\n    * [x] Vectors (AbstractSszVectorSchema)\r\n    * [x] Primitives (AbstractSszPrimitiveSchema) Including trimming data to correct length\r\n    * [ ] Use lazy loading of nodes\r\n* [ ] Optimise if still necessary when not iterating entire trie every slot\r\n* [ ] Optimise sizing of stored node hash cache (to avoid writing unchanged nodes to the db).\r\n    * [ ] Review this in light of the potential for max compression level to change? Probably safe but needs to be thought through.\r\n  * [ ] Check behaviour of import tool when mixing snapshot and trie based state storage migrations (should reject them)\r\n* [ ] Investigate slow shutdown",
